{
  "stem": "15962.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I think children are very sensitive and often cruel about differences.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the difference was primarily manifested when we had religious instructions, which I think only happened once a week.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The school-- this was a state that had separation of religion and state so that during the religious instructions, the Catholics would go to one classroom and the Protestant the other.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I had a hour, a free hour, that I could go and run outside.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Jewish children had religious instructions.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we will learned Hebrew in an old what used to be the Jewish school in the Jewish street in the center of town, where an old cantor taught us how to read.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And also, we had some instructions how to dress the Torah.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That was for the boys.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But other than that, I would visit the synagogue primarily on high holy days with my mother.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And all the big holidays were also celebrated at my uncle's, who was the head of the Jewish community and had a home that observed all the Jewish dietary laws, such as you know, could not eat meat and, and milk products at the same time.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I couldn't tell you exactly, because I was a child then.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But he probably was like the head of the synagogue here, although I think the organization was somewhat different.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was born in a clinic run by Dr.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Ganz, who later immigrated to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And curiously enough, my wife's parents who knew him well because they were living in Palestine.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And many of the, shall we call it, bourgeois families would, would have their children born in this clinic, which was about two hours dis-distance by car from where I lived.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't think it was exclusively Jewish.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
